a/Conducting awareness raising activities in target municipalities;
b/Incorporation of DRR into learning curricula of schools and universities;
c/Networking activities - community awards and community forum organized.
3.3/
a/ Project designs are developed for 3 GCF-funded structural measures and construction initiated (LoA with MRDI);
b/Designs of 5 RD-financed sites finalized and construction initiated;

1.1/
a/ Telecommunication is system procured. The installation will launch in 2022 will be finalized in 2023. An upgrade of the ICT infrastructure beyond telecommunication system (including two additional components of ICT - Weather Forecasting System (WFS) (component 2 of ICT) and Communication and Dissemination systems (component 3 of ICT)) was identified as an urgent need to enable NEA to establish well-functioning Multi-Hazard Early Warning System;
b/ HPC is procured and operationalized; 
c/ Hydrometeorological equipment (more than half) is procured and delivered to NEA. Including: 7 automatic meteorological stations, 50 automatic meteorological posts, 26 automatic hydrological posts and 6 snow measurement stations;
d/ Third tender announced for the procurement of Agrometeorological Stations. Selection process is ongoing;
1.2/
a/ Out of total eight unified methodologies of multi-hazard mapping that includes methods for modelling and mapping of the hazards with specifics, seven are developed and one is to be completed by end of year; 
b/ 92% of LIDAR data is collected and processed. 8% of LIDAR data collected to be process by the end of January 2022;
c/ National level hazard risk models/maps (avalanche, windstorm, hailstorm) and hazard risk models (flood landslide, mudflow), are developed for 3 river basins (Supsa, Kintrishi, Natanebi); 
e/ Historical and field data on hydrometeorological and geological hazards for Enguri, Khobistskali and Mtkvari (left bank in the boundaries of Tbilisi City) rivers were collected and processed. Historical data hydrometeorological and geological field data were collected for Mtkvari (right bank in the boundaries of Tbilisi – Vere, Digmistskali, Dukniskhevi), Rioni and Chorokhi-Adjaristksali river basins were collected and will be processed in the first quarter of 2022; 
1.3/
a/ RPM for floods (developed under prototype Rioni project) has been reactivated and proven by contracted company Geographic;
b/ Pending. Depends on availability of hazard maps developed under SDC project; 
1.4/
a/ Design of the Multi Hazard Disaster Risk Information System (MHDRIS) is developed and agreed;
2.1/
a/ Preparation of legal framework for Risk Knowledge and Preparedness and Response Capabilities components under MHEWS checklist is underway to be finalized in 2023. Recommendations for improvement of legal framework developed to be agreed with national partners. Institutional framework for Risk Knowledge and Preparedness and Response Capabilities components under MHEWS checklist is developed through the results of activities 1.2, 1.4, 2.4. Development of Baseline Capacity Assessment Report for MHEWS is ongoing to be finalized by January 2022.;
b/ Capacity Development Plan for MHEWS will be finalized in March, 2022;
c/ Awareness raising events in CCA/DRR are ongoing.
2.2/
a/ International advice was provided on enhancing meteorological forecasting through improving local model parametrizations and on the quality of satellite precipitation estimates. To further improve meteorological forecasting additional advice will be provided by international expert in meteorology who is expected to start assignment starting from 2022;
b/International advice was provided on integrating new source data/type into forecasting platform. To further advice on relevance of integrating data from various resources into the forecasting platform, additional advice will be provided by international expert in meteorology who is expected to start assignment starting from 2022;
c/International advice was provided on expanding flood forecasting platform through rebuilding hydrological and hydraulic models for Rioni river basin and linking to flood forecasting platform. Both models were validated and operationalized;
2.3/
a/Assessment of National capacities in progress, supported by national international experts; 
b/Pending due to failure of recruitment of international expert;
c/Pending due to failure of recruitment of international expert; 
2.4/
a/ Development of municipal preparedness and response plans by EMS for 4 municipalities out of 11 is initiated and will be finalized in September 2022. Municipal preparedness and response plans by EMS for all eleven municipalities will be finalized by the end of 2023; 
b/ Training of trainers of the EMS staff based on the needs identified within trainings needs assessment report is conducted;
c/ 4 municipal preparedness and response plans will be finalized in September 2022 and remaining 7 will be finalized by the end 2023
3.1/
a, b, c/ Gender specific inputs provided to analysis of Legal and Regulatory Framework for Disaster Risk Knowledge Component of Multi-Hazard Early Warning System in Georgia; Specific sessions on gender were integral part of awareness raising activities e.g. community forum, trainings for local NGOs, etc. Gender disaggregated data was collected. Applying gender mainstreaming was not possible only in case of the project activities that were postponed;
d/ Baseline survey postponed due to the fact that most vulnerable communities have not been identified; 
3.2/
a/Awareness raising activities were conducted in 10 target municipalities;
b/Georgian Institute of Public Affairs (GIPA) has already integrated DRR in the syllabus of environment protection. Negotiations are ongoing with Zugdidi, Telavi and Kutaisi Universities to incorporate DRR in their curricula. Education material for schools were distributed in the public schools at the 10 target municipalities;
c/One community award and one school award were conducted. Two community forums – one online and one in person were organized;
3.3/
a/ Designs for 3 GCF funded sites were developed. LoA with Roads Department (under MRDI) was signed, company for construction works was contracted, construction was initiated. Emergency and Social Management Plan (ESMP) was agreed with GCF;
b/Designs for 5 government funded sites were developed. Roads Department has announced construction tender. Company for construction works was contracted and construction was initiated. ESMP was agreed with GCF.
